OL,3,CAurigny confirms #6.5 million loss in
OL,4,C2024 after 'challenging year'
OL,6,FThe Guernsey airline Aurigny lost #6.5
OL,7,Fmillion in 2024, despite handling a
OL,8,Frecord number of passengers.
OL,10,FThe government-owned operator says its
OL,11,Fexpenditure was driven by the
OL,12,Funexpected cost of leasing aircraft to
OL,13,Fcover technical problems that kept
OL,14,Fsome of its fleet grounded last year,
OL,15,Fas well as global supply chain issues.
OL,17,FAurigny adds that it avoided #10
OL,18,Fmillion of maintenance costs by
OL,19,Fselling the 122-seater Embraer jet.
