OL,3,CAurigny confirms #6.5 million loss in
OL,4,C2024 after 'challenging year'
OL,6,FRoger Pratt, the airline's Chief
OL,7,FFinancial Officer, explains: "The
OL,8,Fshort-term pressures we faced in 2024,
OL,9,Fparticularly the need for significant
OL,10,Fwet leasing, are easing and the
OL,11,Fdecisions made last year - including
OL,12,Ffleet simplification - will help
OL,13,Fsecure longer-term financial stability.
OL,15,F"Whilst this was a challenging year
OL,16,Fthat in many ways both Aurigny and its
OL,17,Fpassengers will wish to put behind
OL,18,Fthem, we connected more people than
OL,19,Fever before, supported the island's
OL,20,Fvisitor economy, and protected
OL,21,Fessential lifeline routes."
