OL,3,CAurigny confirms #6.5 million loss in
OL,4,C2024 after 'challenging year'
OL,6,FThe airline dealt with 570,000
OL,7,Fpassengers in 2024, 3% more than the
OL,8,Fprevious year.
OL,10,FDeputy Peter Roffey, the outgoing
OL,11,FPresident of Guernsey's States Trading
OL,12,FSupervisory Board, spoke about the
OL,13,Fsituation in April, describing
OL,14,FAurigny's 2024 performance as "a
OL,15,Ffairly disastrous year".
OL,17,FHowever, he added that previous strong
OL,18,Fearnings mean the airline will not be
OL,19,Fasking the taxpayer for extra funding.
